[stdout] {"type":"text","timestamp":1772606904025,"sessionID":"ses_3486a135effe8wV3Ecxb54k0Uy","part":{"id":"prt_cb79ab9c7001wE8j9HSl7ynJK3","sessionID":"ses_3486a135effe8wV3Ecxb54k0Uy","messageID":"msg_cb79ab062001qafvtnYqc3eJXJ","type":"text","text":"Implemented a minimal RP2040 breakout board using tscircuit with `routingDisabled` and JLCPCB-imported core parts, then ran the required build command.\n\n- Updated `index.circuit.tsx` to define a compact breakout with:\n  - RP2040 (`C2040`) from `imports/RP2040.tsx`\n  - USB-C connector (`C165948`) from `imports/TYPE_C_31_M_12.tsx`\n  - 3.3V regulator (`C6186`) from `imports/AMS1117_3_3.tsx`\n  - Status LED + resistor, CC pull-down resistors, and basic decoupling/regulator caps\n- Disabled autorouting at board level with `<board ... routingDisabled>` in `index.circuit.tsx`.\n- Kept all imported IC/connector/regulator components sourced via `tsci import --jlcpcb` and did not add any tscircuit registry package components.\n- Used explicit net-based connectivity for USB data/CC/power and RP2040 supply domains to match `routingDisabled` behavior.\n- Ran `tsci build --site --use-cdn-javascript` as requested; output is generated in `dist/index/circuit.json` and `dist/index.html`.\n\nAssumptions used:\n- A minimal breakout is interpreted as RP2040 + USB power/data path + onboard LED indicator + essential power support components, without full production-level RP2040 support circuitry (e.g., external QSPI flash, crystal, full boot/reset/debug header set).\n\nBuild status:\n- Build generated site artifacts in `dist/`.\n- Build reports 2 overlap DRC errors (`pcb_smtpad overlaps pcb_smtpad`), likely originating from the imported USB-C footprint geometry in `imports/TYPE_C_31_M_12.tsx`.","time":{"start":1772606904023,"end":1772606904023}}}

